Sentencas: Large footprint (144 cm(2)) cells with infiltrated (La0.6Sr0.4)(0.95)FeO3/yttria-stabilized zirconia (LSF-YSZ) cathodes were fabricated on a pre-production scale (approximately 90 cells/batch).
Titulo: Characterization and Stack Testing of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Cathodes Prepared by Infiltration

Sentencas: The excellent electrochemical performance of the cells was confirmed both on single cell as well as on stack level.
Titulo: Characterization and Stack Testing of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Cathodes Prepared by Infiltration

Sentencas: Changes in electrode properties were mapped out as a function of heat-treatment temperature.
Titulo: Characterization and Stack Testing of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Cathodes Prepared by Infiltration

Sentencas: The microstructure of the porous zirconia backbone remained unchanged, but the surface area of the ferrite phase decreased gradually, as the electrode was treated to higher temperatures.
Titulo: Characterization and Stack Testing of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Cathodes Prepared by Infiltration

Sentencas: Changes in surface area were accompanied by corresponding changes in pore size and total pore volume.
Titulo: Characterization and Stack Testing of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Cathodes Prepared by Infiltration

Sentencas: In contrast to traditional composite electrodes, the in-plane conductivity of infiltrated LSF-YSZ cathodes decreased with increasing sintering temperature, a trend likely explained by microstructure alterations during the sintering of the non-random structure.
Titulo: Characterization and Stack Testing of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Cathodes Prepared by Infiltration
